{"questionId":"22767","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Katie likes to cycle to work as much as possible. If Katie cycles to work one day then she has&nbsp;a probability of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn></math> of not cycling to work on the next work day. If she does not cycle to work&nbsp;one day then she has a probability of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>4</mn></math> of not cycling to work on the next work day.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Katie works for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>180</mn></math> days in a year.</p>\n<p>Find the probability that Katie cycles to work on her final working day of the year.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">A</mi><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>8</mn></mtd><mtd><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>6</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn></mtd><mtd><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>4</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">A</mi><mn>180</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>75</mn></mtd><mtd><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>75</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>25</mn></mtd><mtd><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>25</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>75</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong><br>[3 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"22767","referenceCode":"21N.1.AHL.TZ0.9b","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-appli